== Legacy ==

The DVD was released in 2003 and contains many extra features, such as extensive interviews with DuBowski and Rabbi Steven Greenberg. There is also a mini-documentary about reactions to the film around the world and what happened to the people who were featured in the documentary.<ref>[http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0000BV1YO/ Amazon.com's listing of ''Trembling before G-d'', with DVD details]. Retrieved [[March 7]], [[2007]].</ref> The total running time for the special features is actually over 2 hours longer than the documentary itself.<ref name="DVD verdict" />

With a seed grant from [[Steven Spielberg]], the creators of the film have set up the Trembling Before G-d Orthodox Education Project, to teach Orthodox educators and rabbis about homosexuality,<ref name="USA" /> as well as convening the first Orthodox [[Mental health|Mental Health]] Conference on Homosexuality and training facilitators to show the film to community leaders.<ref>Tremblingbeforeg-d.com, [http://www.tremblingbeforeg-d.com/resources/index.html Trembling Before G-d: Resources]. Retrieved [[March 9]], [[2007]].</ref> Over 2000 principals, educators and school counselors have attended screenings within Israel's [[Parochial school|religious school]] system.<ref>Clal.org, [http://www.clal.org/clal_faculty_sg.html CLAL Faculty: Steven Greenberg]. Retrieved [[March 9]], [[2007]].</ref> The film has now been seen by an estimated 8 million people worldwide.<ref name="BAR"/> Following the success of ''Trembling before G-d'', DuBowski is now working to produce a documentary about gay devout Muslims entitled ''[[A Jihad for Love]]''.<ref name="BAR">Hartleyfoundation.org, [http://hartleyfoundation.org/development/in_the_name_of_Allah.php A Jihad for Love]. Retrieved [[April 1]], [[2007]].</ref>

